article.headline: Deveny grabs double-double in comeback
article.linkText: No. 24 Boston College holds off Liberty in overtime
article.story:
PROVIDENCE, Rhode Island (Ticker) -- Jessalyn Deveny scored 
five of her 20 points within the final 90 seconds of regulation,
and No. 24 Boston College went on to beat Liberty in overtime,
74-70, in the first round of the Brown Classic.

Deveny converted three free throws with 1:24 left in regulation
to bring her team within two points at 64-62. After the Lady
Flames turned the ball over on their next possession, Deveny
sunk a jumper with four seconds remaining to force overtime.

A recent Big East Co-Player of the Week, Deveny finished
8-for-18 from the floor and grabbed 10 rebounds for the Eagles
(6-0), who led by as many as six points in the extra session.

Amber Jacobs, who also posted 20 points for Boston College, went
3-for-5 from 3-point range and 5-for-5 from the foul line. She
recorded seven assists and three steals and Lisa Macchia chipped
in with 11 points and three blocks for the Eagles.

Katie Feenstra produced 25 points and 13 points to post her
third straight double-double for the Lady Flames (2-4), who led,
30-28, at halftime.
